body: Prowler’s death was so fucking stupid. Aside from making no logical sense in both outfit design and where he was shot, it was clearly done just to make Miles have a family member tragically die to motivate him instead of just… You know… Continuing with the motivation he already had, as well as the tension of the most badass villain also being his uncle?

summary: With Spider-Man AND Stranger Things coming out next week, spoilers are going to be everywhere. As usual, tag your spoilers. It’s...
body:
With Spider-Man AND Stranger Things coming out next week, spoilers are going to be everywhere. As usual, tag your spoilers. It’s not hard and it doesn’t hurt. This include reblogs too. My dumbass only just recently found that out. Tag your reblogs too if they include spoilers.

That being said, if you want to avoid spoilers, filter your tags. Not everyone will tag them though. Sometimes people will forget or they don’t care. I honestly would suggest getting off social media if you are 100% sure you don’t want to see anything.

And finally, don’t suggest people to not post about it just because you haven’t seen it. Nothing wrong with that. You have reasons and it’s okay. Millions of people are going to watch either of these things and it’d be hard to not talk about this.

I’m only posting this because I’ve had several anon attacks for posting spoilers. I’ve tagged them and I’ve even placed a warning before typing. I’m expecting a shit more of them next week. But I’m not gonna avoid talking about it. I’ll tag and give warnings, but don’t get mad at me or anyone else if you stumbled upon spoilers without taking precautions.
